<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="MTA56">
<l>pērē varappitaṟṟa lallālem pemmāṉai</l>
<l>yārē yaṟivā ratuniṟka – nērē</l>
<l>kaṭikkamalat tuḷḷiruntuṅ kāṇkilāṉ kaṇṇa</l>
<l>ṉaṭikkamalan taṉṉai yayaṉ</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Besides babbling so that just [his] names come [out], who will be those</l>
<l>who know our Lord? Let that rest. [Even] the Unborn one,</l>
<l>despite sitting in the fragrant lotus<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">Or, with a different positiong of nērē: “despite sitting directly in the fragrant lotus”</note>, cannot directly see<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">For negative with kil-tal as an auxiliary see also Po. 45.2 and Pū. 16.4.</note></l>
<l>the foot lotuses of Kaṇṇaṉ.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
